## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites

| Tool | Version |
|---|---|
| Python | 3.9 or higher |
| Node.js | 18 or higher |
| npm | 8 or higher |

---

### Step 1 — Get a Groq API Key

1. Go to https://console.groq.com
2. Sign up / log in
3. Click **API Keys** → **Create API Key**
4. Copy the key — you will need it in Step 2

---

### Step 2 — Set up the Backend

```bash
# Navigate to backend folder
cd encegen-project/backend

# Install Python dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Create your .env file from the example
cp .env.example .env
```

Now open `.env` and fill in your values:

```env
# Required — your Groq API key
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_groq_api_key_here

# Email notifications (GoDaddy SMTP)
GODADDY_USER=noreply@encegenailabs.com
GODADDY_PASS=YourGoDaddyEmailPassword
GODADDY_TO=sales@encegenailabs.com
```

Start the backend server:

```bash
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload
```

Backend is running at http://localhost:8000

---

### Step 3 — Set up the Frontend

```bash
# Navigate to frontend folder
cd encegen-project/frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start development server
npm run dev
```

Frontend is running at http://localhost:5173

Open your browser — you will see the floating chatbot button in the bottom-right corner.

---

### Step 4 — Add Your Company Logo

Place your logo file here:
```
frontend/public/Encegen_logo.jpg
```

> The filename must be exactly `Encegen_logo.jpg` (capital E).
> The logo appears in the main header as a rounded square icon.

---

## 🔧 Environment Variables

### Backend — `backend/.env`

| Variable | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `GROQ_API_KEY` | Yes | Your Groq API key from console.groq.com |
| `GODADDY_USER` | Optional | GoDaddy SMTP sender email |
| `GODADDY_PASS` | Optional | GoDaddy email password |
| `GODADDY_TO` | Optional | Email address to receive notifications |

### Frontend — `frontend/.env` (create if needed)

| Variable | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `VITE_API_URL` | Only if backend is on a different domain | e.g. https://api.yourdomain.com |

---

## 🏗️ Build for Production

### Build the frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm run build
```

This creates a `frontend/dist/` folder with compiled files.

### Run the backend in production

```bash
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 2
```

### Embed in your existing website

After building, copy the `dist/assets/` files to your server and add to your HTML:

```html
<!-- Just before </body> -->
<div id="enci-root"></div>
<link  rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/index-[hash].css" />
<script type="module"   src="/assets/index-[hash].js"></script>
```

Replace `[hash]` with the actual filename shown after running `npm run build`.

---

## 🌐 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | /api/chat | Send a message, get AI response |
| POST | /api/leads | Save a qualified lead |
| GET | /api/leads | List all leads |
| POST | /api/bookings | Create a meeting booking |
| GET | /api/bookings | List all bookings |
| GET | /admin | Admin dashboard |
| GET | /api/stats | Lead and booking statistics |

---

## 🤖 Chatbot Behaviour

### Conversation Flow (3-4 steps)

```
Step 1 → Greet and understand the user's need
Step 2 → Clarify with one focused question
Step 3 → Collect contact details (name + phone/email)
Step 4 → Suggest booking a free Discovery Meeting
```

### Special Responses

| Situation | Enci's Response |
|---|---|
| Off-topic (weather, news) | "I'm Enci, Encegen AI Labs' dedicated AI Assistant. I'm not able to help with that..." |
| Incomplete message | "I'm sorry, I didn't quite understand that. Would you like help with AI Solutions or Services?" |
| Sensitive info requested | "I cannot provide that information. Please contact sales@encegenailabs.com" |

### Lead Validation Rules

A lead is only saved when ALL of these are true:

- User has sent at least 4 messages
- User has shared their full name
- User has shared a phone number (10 digits) or email address
- User has shown genuine interest in a specific service

---

## 🎨 Customisation

### Change brand colors

Open `EncegenChatWidget.jsx` and edit the `C` object at the top:

```js
const C = {
  accent:    "#6C2FFF",   // Main purple — change to your brand color
  accentSub: "#00C8FF",   // Cyan accent
  // ...
};
```

### Change company info

Edit the `CO` object in `EncegenChatWidget.jsx`:

```js
const CO = {
  email:   "sales@encegenailabs.com",
  website: "https://encegen.in",
  phone1:  { name: "Navneet Acharya", num: "7030555120" },
  // ...
};
```

### Change the AI system prompt

Edit `SYSTEM_PROMPT` in `backend/main.py` to change Enci's personality and responses.

---

## 📧 Email Setup

The chatbot sends email notifications when:
- A new lead is captured from a conversation
- A meeting booking is confirmed

See `EMAIL_SETUP.md` for full GoDaddy SMTP configuration instructions.

---

## 🛡️ Production Checklist

- [ ] Set GROQ_API_KEY in backend/.env
- [ ] Set GODADDY_USER, GODADDY_PASS, GODADDY_TO for email alerts
- [ ] Place Encegen_logo.jpg in frontend/public/
- [ ] Set VITE_API_URL if backend is on a different domain
- [ ] Run backend behind nginx or caddy with HTTPS
- [ ] Update allow_origins in backend/main.py to your domain
- [ ] Run npm run build and deploy dist/ to your web server

---

## 🗂️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend | React 18, Vite 5 |
| Backend | Python 3.11, FastAPI, Uvicorn |
| AI Model | Groq — LLaMA 3.1-8B-Instant |
| Database | SQLite (via aiosqlite) |
| Email | GoDaddy SMTP (aiosmtplib) |
| Styling | Pure inline styles + CSS keyframes |

